AB  - Previous cost–benefit studies of residential time-of-use rates have relied on widely varying methods, many of which are incomplete. In this article, the authors develop a comprehensive methodology for analyzing residential time-of-use rates and contrast this methodology with the approaches previously taken. They apply this methodology to a study of residential time-of-use rates are not cost justified. Furthermore, they show the large errors that can result from using the incomplete approaches.
